57// By default, release builds don't log, debug builds at info level
58#if !defined(NDEBUG)
59static LoggingSeverity g_min_sev = LS_INFO;
60static LoggingSeverity g_dbg_sev = LS_INFO;
61#else
62static LoggingSeverity g_min_sev = LS_NONE;
63static LoggingSeverity g_dbg_sev = LS_NONE;
64#endif

66// Return the filename portion of the string (that following the last slash).
67const char* FilenameFromPath(const char* file) {
68 const char* end1 = ::strrchr(file, '/');
69 const char* end2 = ::strrchr(file, '\\');
70 if (!end1 && !end2)
71 return file;
72 else
73 return (end1 > end2) ? end1 + 1 : end2 + 1;
74}
75
76// Global lock for log subsystem, only needed to serialize access to streams_.
77// TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11665): this is not currently constant initialized and
78// trivially destructible.
79webrtc::Mutex& logMutex() {
80 static auto mutex = NeverDestroyed<webrtc::Mutex>();
81 return mutex.get();
82}

92bool LogMessage::log_to_stderr_ = true;
93
94// The list of logging streams currently configured.
95// Note: we explicitly do not clean this up, because of the uncertain ordering
96// of destructors at program exit. Let the person who sets the stream trigger
97// cleanup by setting to null, or let it leak (safe at program exit).
98ABSL_CONST_INIT LogSink* LogMessage::streams_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(logMutex()) =
99 nullptr;
100ABSL_CONST_INIT std::atomic<bool> LogMessage::streams_empty_ = {true};
101
102// Boolean options default to false (0)
103bool LogMessage::thread_, LogMessage::timestamp_;
104
105LogMessage::LogMessage(const char* file, int line, LoggingSeverity sev)
106 : LogMessage(file, line, sev, ERRCTX_NONE, 0) {}
107
108LogMessage::LogMessage(const char* file,
109 int line,
110 LoggingSeverity sev,
111 LogErrorContext err_ctx,
112 int err)
113 : severity_(sev) {
114 if (timestamp_) {
115 // Use SystemTimeMillis so that even if tests use fake clocks, the timestamp
116 // in log messages represents the real system time.
117 int64_t time = TimeDiff(SystemTimeMillis(), LogStartTime());
118 // Also ensure WallClockStartTime is initialized, so that it matches
119 // LogStartTime.
120 WallClockStartTime();
121 // TODO(kwiberg): Switch to absl::StrFormat, if binary size is ok.
122 char timestamp[50]; // Maximum string length of an int64_t is 20.
123 int len =
124 snprintf(timestamp, sizeof(timestamp), "[%03" PRId64 ":%03" PRId64 "]",
125 time / 1000, time % 1000);
126 RTC_DCHECK_LT(len, sizeof(timestamp));
127 print_stream_ << timestamp;
128 }
129
130 if (thread_) {
131 PlatformThreadId id = CurrentThreadId();
132 print_stream_ << "[" << id << "] ";
133 }
134
135 if (file != nullptr) {
136#if defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
137 tag_ = FilenameFromPath(file);
138 print_stream_ << "(line " << line << "): ";
139#else
140 print_stream_ << "(" << FilenameFromPath(file) << ":" << line << "): ";
141#endif
142 }
143
144 if (err_ctx != ERRCTX_NONE) {
145 char tmp_buf[1024];
146 SimpleStringBuilder tmp(tmp_buf);
147 tmp.AppendFormat("[0x%08X]", err);
148 switch (err_ctx) {
149 case ERRCTX_ERRNO:
150 tmp << " " << strerror(err);
151 break;
152#ifdef WEBRTC_WIN
153 case ERRCTX_HRESULT: {
154 char msgbuf[256];
155 DWORD flags =
156 FORMAT_MESSAGE_FROM_SYSTEM | FORMAT_MESSAGE_IGNORE_INSERTS;
157 if (DWORD len = FormatMessageA(
158 flags, nullptr, err, MAKELANGID(LANG_NEUTRAL, SUBLANG_DEFAULT),
159 msgbuf, sizeof(msgbuf) / sizeof(msgbuf[0]), nullptr)) {
160 while ((len > 0) &&
161 isspace(static_cast<unsigned char>(msgbuf[len - 1]))) {
162 msgbuf[--len] = 0;
163 }
164 tmp << " " << msgbuf;
165 }
166 break;
167 }
168#endif // WEBRTC_WIN
169 default:
170 break;
171 }
172 extra_ = tmp.str();
173 }
174}

187// DEPRECATED. Currently only used by downstream projects that use
188// implementation details of logging.h. Work is ongoing to remove those
189// dependencies.
190LogMessage::LogMessage(const char* file,
191 int line,
192 LoggingSeverity sev,
193 const std::string& tag)
194 : LogMessage(file, line, sev) {
195 print_stream_ << tag << ": ";
196}
197
198LogMessage::~LogMessage() {
199 FinishPrintStream();
200
201 const std::string str = print_stream_.Release();
202
203 if (severity_ >= g_dbg_sev) {
204#if defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
205 OutputToDebug(str, severity_, tag_);
206#else
207 OutputToDebug(str, severity_);
208#endif
209 }
210
211 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&logMutex());
212 for (LogSink* entry = streams_; entry != nullptr; entry = entry->next_) {
213 if (severity_ >= entry->min_severity_) {
214#if defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
215 entry->OnLogMessage(str, severity_, tag_);
216#else
217 entry->OnLogMessage(str, severity_);
218#endif
219 }
220 }
221}

278
279int LogMessage::GetLogToStream(LogSink* stream) {
280 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&logMutex());
281 LoggingSeverity sev = LS_NONE;
282 for (LogSink* entry = streams_; entry != nullptr; entry = entry->next_) {
283 if (stream == nullptr || stream == entry) {
284 sev = std::min(sev, entry->min_severity_);
285 }
286 }
287 return sev;
288}
289
290void LogMessage::AddLogToStream(LogSink* stream, LoggingSeverity min_sev) {
291 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&logMutex());
292 stream->min_severity_ = min_sev;
293 stream->next_ = streams_;
294 streams_ = stream;
295 streams_empty_.store(false, std::memory_order_relaxed);
296 UpdateMinLogSeverity();
297}
298
299void LogMessage::RemoveLogToStream(LogSink* stream) {
300 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&logMutex());
301 for (LogSink** entry = &streams_; *entry != nullptr;
302 entry = &(*entry)->next_) {
303 if (*entry == stream) {
304 *entry = (*entry)->next_;
305 break;
306 }
307 }
308 streams_empty_.store(streams_ == nullptr, std::memory_order_relaxed);
309 UpdateMinLogSeverity();
310}
311
312void LogMessage::ConfigureLogging(const char* params) {
313 LoggingSeverity current_level = LS_VERBOSE;
314 LoggingSeverity debug_level = GetLogToDebug();
315
316 std::vector<std::string> tokens;
317 tokenize(params, ' ', &tokens);
318
319 for (const std::string& token : tokens) {
320 if (token.empty())
321 continue;
322
323 // Logging features
324 if (token == "tstamp") {
325 LogTimestamps();
326 } else if (token == "thread") {
327 LogThreads();
328
329 // Logging levels
330 } else if (token == "verbose") {
331 current_level = LS_VERBOSE;
332 } else if (token == "info") {
333 current_level = LS_INFO;
334 } else if (token == "warning") {
335 current_level = LS_WARNING;
336 } else if (token == "error") {
337 current_level = LS_ERROR;
338 } else if (token == "none") {
339 current_level = LS_NONE;
340
341 // Logging targets
342 } else if (token == "debug") {
343 debug_level = current_level;
344 }
345 }
346
347#if defined(WEBRTC_WIN) && !defined(WINUWP)
348 if ((LS_NONE != debug_level) && !::IsDebuggerPresent()) {
349 // First, attempt to attach to our parent's console... so if you invoke
350 // from the command line, we'll see the output there. Otherwise, create
351 // our own console window.
352 // Note: These methods fail if a console already exists, which is fine.
353 if (!AttachConsole(ATTACH_PARENT_PROCESS))
354 ::AllocConsole();
355 }
356#endif // defined(WEBRTC_WIN) && !defined(WINUWP)
357
358 LogToDebug(debug_level);
359}
360
361void LogMessage::UpdateMinLogSeverity()
362 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(logMutex()) {
363 LoggingSeverity min_sev = g_dbg_sev;
364 for (LogSink* entry = streams_; entry != nullptr; entry = entry->next_) {
365 min_sev = std::min(min_sev, entry->min_severity_);
366 }
367 g_min_sev = min_sev;
368}
369
370#if defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
371void LogMessage::OutputToDebug(const std::string& str,
372 LoggingSeverity severity,
373 const char* tag) {
374#else
375void LogMessage::OutputToDebug(const std::string& str,
376 LoggingSeverity severity) {
377#endif
378 bool log_to_stderr = log_to_stderr_;
379#if defined(WEBRTC_MAC) && !defined(WEBRTC_IOS) && defined(NDEBUG)
380 // On the Mac, all stderr output goes to the Console log and causes clutter.
381 // So in opt builds, don't log to stderr unless the user specifically sets
382 // a preference to do so.
383 CFStringRef key = CFStringCreateWithCString(
384 kCFAllocatorDefault, "logToStdErr", kCFStringEncodingUTF8);
385 CFStringRef domain = CFBundleGetIdentifier(CFBundleGetMainBundle());
386 if (key != nullptr && domain != nullptr) {
387 Boolean exists_and_is_valid;
388 Boolean should_log =
389 CFPreferencesGetAppBooleanValue(key, domain, &exists_and_is_valid);
390 // If the key doesn't exist or is invalid or is false, we will not log to
391 // stderr.
392 log_to_stderr = exists_and_is_valid && should_log;
393 }
394 if (key != nullptr) {
395 CFRelease(key);
396 }
397#endif // defined(WEBRTC_MAC) && !defined(WEBRTC_IOS) && defined(NDEBUG)
398
399#if defined(WEBRTC_WIN)
400 // Always log to the debugger.
401 // Perhaps stderr should be controlled by a preference, as on Mac?
402 OutputDebugStringA(str.c_str());
403 if (log_to_stderr) {
404 // This handles dynamically allocated consoles, too.
405 if (HANDLE error_handle = ::GetStdHandle(STD_ERROR_HANDLE)) {
406 log_to_stderr = false;
407 DWORD written = 0;
408 ::WriteFile(error_handle, str.data(), static_cast<DWORD>(str.size()),
409 &written, 0);
410 }
411 }
412#endif // WEBRTC_WIN
413
414#if defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
415 // Android's logging facility uses severity to log messages but we
416 // need to map libjingle's severity levels to Android ones first.
417 // Also write to stderr which maybe available to executable started
418 // from the shell.
419 int prio;
420 switch (severity) {
421 case LS_VERBOSE:
422 prio = ANDROID_LOG_VERBOSE;
423 break;
424 case LS_INFO:
425 prio = ANDROID_LOG_INFO;
426 break;
427 case LS_WARNING:
428 prio = ANDROID_LOG_WARN;
429 break;
430 case LS_ERROR:
431 prio = ANDROID_LOG_ERROR;
432 break;
433 default:
434 prio = ANDROID_LOG_UNKNOWN;
435 }
436
437 int size = str.size();
438 int line = 0;
439 int idx = 0;
440 const int max_lines = size / kMaxLogLineSize + 1;
441 if (max_lines == 1) {
442 __android_log_print(prio, tag, "%.*s", size, str.c_str());
443 } else {
444 while (size > 0) {
445 const int len = std::min(size, kMaxLogLineSize);
446 // Use the size of the string in the format (str may have \0 in the
447 // middle).
448 __android_log_print(prio, tag, "[%d/%d] %.*s", line + 1, max_lines, len,
449 str.c_str() + idx);
450 idx += len;
451 size -= len;
452 ++line;
453 }
454 }
455#endif // WEBRTC_ANDROID
456 if (g_log_output_callback) {
457 g_log_output_callback(severity, str.c_str());
458 }
459 if (log_to_stderr) {
460 fprintf(stderr, "%s", str.c_str());
461 fflush(stderr);
462 }
463}
464
465// static
466bool LogMessage::IsNoop(LoggingSeverity severity) {
467 if (severity >= g_dbg_sev || severity >= g_min_sev)
468 return false;
469 return streams_empty_.load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
470}
471
472void LogMessage::FinishPrintStream() {
473 if (!extra_.empty())
474 print_stream_ << " : " << extra_;
475 print_stream_ << "\n";
476}

478namespace webrtc_logging_impl {
479
480void Log(const LogArgType* fmt, ...) {
481 va_list args;
482 va_start(args, fmt);
483
484 LogMetadataErr meta;
485 const char* tag = nullptr;
486 switch (*fmt) {
487 case LogArgType::kLogMetadata: {
488 meta = {va_arg(args, LogMetadata), ERRCTX_NONE, 0};
489 break;
490 }
491 case LogArgType::kLogMetadataErr: {
492 meta = va_arg(args, LogMetadataErr);
493 break;
494 }
495#ifdef WEBRTC_ANDROID
496 case LogArgType::kLogMetadataTag: {
497 const LogMetadataTag tag_meta = va_arg(args, LogMetadataTag);
498 meta = {{nullptr, 0, tag_meta.severity}, ERRCTX_NONE, 0};
499 tag = tag_meta.tag;
500 break;
501 }
502#endif
503 default: {
504 RTC_NOTREACHED();
505 va_end(args);
506 return;
507 }
508 }
509
510 LogMessage log_message(meta.meta.File(), meta.meta.Line(),
511 meta.meta.Severity(), meta.err_ctx, meta.err);
512 if (tag) {
513 log_message.AddTag(tag);
514 }
515
516 for (++fmt; *fmt != LogArgType::kEnd; ++fmt) {
517 switch (*fmt) {
518 case LogArgType::kInt:
519 log_message.stream() << va_arg(args, int);
520 break;
521 case LogArgType::kLong:
522 log_message.stream() << va_arg(args, long);
523 break;
524 case LogArgType::kLongLong:
525 log_message.stream() << va_arg(args, long long);
526 break;
527 case LogArgType::kUInt:
528 log_message.stream() << va_arg(args, unsigned);
529 break;
530 case LogArgType::kULong:
531 log_message.stream() << va_arg(args, unsigned long);
532 break;
533 case LogArgType::kULongLong:
534 log_message.stream() << va_arg(args, unsigned long long);
535 break;
536 case LogArgType::kDouble:
537 log_message.stream() << va_arg(args, double);
538 break;
539 case LogArgType::kLongDouble:
540 log_message.stream() << va_arg(args, long double);
541 break;
542 case LogArgType::kCharP: {
543 const char* s = va_arg(args, const char*);
544 log_message.stream() << (s ? s : "(null)");
545 break;
546 }
547 case LogArgType::kStdString:
548 log_message.stream() << *va_arg(args, const std::string*);
549 break;
550 case LogArgType::kStringView:
551 log_message.stream() << *va_arg(args, const absl::string_view*);
552 break;
553 case LogArgType::kVoidP:
554 log_message.stream() << rtc::ToHex(
555 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(va_arg(args, const void*)));
556 break;
557 default:
558 RTC_NOTREACHED();
559 va_end(args);
560 return;
561 }
562 }
563
564 va_end(args);
565}

571namespace rtc {
572// Inefficient default implementation, override is recommended.
573void LogSink::OnLogMessage(const std::string& msg,
574 LoggingSeverity severity,
575 const char* tag) {
576 OnLogMessage(tag + (": " + msg), severity);
577}
578
579void LogSink::OnLogMessage(const std::string& msg,
580 LoggingSeverity /* severity */) {
581 OnLogMessage(msg);
582}
